# UI-only TLS front using Caddy's internal CA.
#
# For LAN / private deployments where the host is NOT reachable from the public
# internet (so Let's Encrypt can't validate a domain). Caddy serves the
# management UI over HTTPS with a certificate issued by its own local CA — no
# DNS, no ACME challenge, no internet required. The repository stays on plain
# HTTP (apt's integrity comes from the GPG signature, not the transport).
#
# One hostname is enough: https://<host> → UI (here), http://<host> → repo.
#
# After first start, trust Caddy's root certificate on the devices you browse
# the UI from — see docs/DEPLOYMENT.md ("Trusting the internal CA").

{$WEBUI_DOMAIN} {
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy webui:8000
}
